Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi announced on Sunday that his department had received the much-anticipated forensic investigation report into the drowning of Grade 8 Parktown Boys' High pupil Enock Mpianzi. A preliminary report by the department found that the Grade 8 orientation camp was not approved by the district and head offices.Mpianzi was laid to rest on February 1.The school's principal, Malcolm Williams, has been suspended pending the investigation into the matter.   Source: Â https://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/gauteng-education-dept-has-received-forensic-report-into-enock-mpianzi-death-lesufi-20200216 